              <strong>Important:</strong>
              <p>Not all small hobby breeders are required to hold a USDA AWA license — the requirement applies to breeders who sell more than $500/year in animals commercially. If a breeder is exempt (very small scale, non-commercial), they should be able to explain why clearly. For any breeder claiming commercial scale or professional status, the license should exist and be verifiable.</p>
