          <h3>The "PayPal Friends &amp; Family" Trick</h3>
          <p>Many scammers specifically request PayPal Friends &amp; Family instead of Goods &amp; Services. The difference: Goods &amp; Services includes PayPal Purchase Protection — the buyer can file a dispute and recover funds. Friends &amp; Family does not. It is designed for personal transfers between people who know each other. A seller requesting it is explicitly asking you to waive your protection. Refuse — or switch to a credit card directly.</p>

